"Rev:A0-2" and "Made In China" is silkscreened on the board in the FCC photos. The WiSoC used is an AR1321-AL1A. Default settings are per the FCC manual. The '''XXXX''' in the default SSID pattern appears to be lower-case hex digits. :The FCC label, however, specifies the default SSID pattern as '''TRENDnet732XXXX'''. ''(The board contain a 4-pin UART (serial) output, as well as a 14-pin output (possibly for JTAG?).''
''Headers are unpopulated, need to be soldered.
